<item>
            <title>[TEXT-130] JaroWinklerDistance: Wrong results due to precision of transpositions</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/TEXT-130</link>
                <project id="12318221" key="TEXT">Commons Text</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The method &lt;tt&gt;JaroWinklerDistance#matches&lt;/tt&gt; returns &lt;tt&gt;transpositions / 2&lt;/tt&gt; as integer. However, it is not granted for &lt;tt&gt;transpositions&lt;/tt&gt; to be even. E.g. comparing &quot;aaabcd&quot; and &quot;aaacdb&quot; will result in &lt;tt&gt;transpositions&lt;/tt&gt; = 3. Therefore the method must return 1.5, not 1. Otherwise the similarity is 0.9611111111111111 instead of 0.9416666666666667.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I recommend to return &lt;tt&gt;halfTranspositions&lt;/tt&gt; instead of &lt;tt&gt;transpositions&lt;/tt&gt; and doing the cast and division (&lt;tt&gt;(double) mtp&lt;span class=&quot;error&quot;&gt;&amp;#91;1&amp;#93;&lt;/span&gt; / 2&lt;/tt&gt;) in &lt;tt&gt;JaroWinklerDistance#apply&lt;/tt&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
